      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 used under a documented quality management system with version-controlled input decks; FDA internal QMS procedures applied to in-house Python post-processing scripts.",
      "rationale": "All three modeling organizations (FDA OSEL, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) operated under documented QMS frameworks. Version control (Git) applied to all input decks and post-processing scripts. Ansys solver release notes reviewed for known issues relevant to contact-dominated implicit static analyses. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2 for Medium model risk."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems with analytical solutions (cantilever beam, Hertzian contact) reproduced within 1% for each participating solver configuration.",
      "rationale": "Cantilever beam bending and Hertzian contact benchmark problems solved by each modeling team prior to pedicle-screw analyses. All results within 0.6% of analytical solutions. Code verification documented in supplementary verification report appended to submission package."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates <2% change in all three QoIs between penultimate and final mesh refinement levels; GCI < 5%.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the non-cannulated screw geometry. Stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement all showed <1.4% change between levels 2 and 3. Grid convergence index computed per Roache (1994): GCI < 2.1% for all QoIs. Achieved level 3 reflects systematic Richardson extrapolation documentation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Force and displacement residuals converge below 1e-4 relative norm; energy criterion satisfied at each load step.",
      "rationale": "Implicit Newton-Raphson solver residuals monitored at every load increment. All analyses converged with force residual norm < 5e-5 and displacement residual norm < 3e-5. No spurious contact oscillations detected. Energy balance verified post-solution. Achieved level 2 exceeds the required level 1."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup by analyst not involved in primary build; checklist-based review covering boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions.",
      "rationale": "Each participating organization conducted an independent internal peer review of model inputs, boundary conditions, and contact pair definitions using a standardized checklist aligned with ASME V&V 40 Table 1. Discrepancies identified during review were corrected prior to analysis runs. Review records retained in project dossier."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum linear-elastic with isotropic hardening plasticity; frictional contact (mu=0.2) at screw-block interface; large-displacement formulation enabled. Model form justified by prior literature and material characterization data.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V modeled as elastic-perfectly-plastic with bilinear isotropic hardening; Young's modulus 114 GPa, yield strength 880 MPa from coupon testing. Large-displacement (NLGEOM ON) formulation captures geometric nonlinearity under 40 mm displacement. Frictional contact (Coulomb, mu=0.2) at all metal-on-metal interfaces. Model form consistent with FDA guidance on metallic implant FEA and prior published pedicle screw models. Sensitivity of QoIs to friction coefficient explored in UQ campaign (described in ValidationResult narratives); influence modest (<3% on stiffness)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties derived from lot-specific coupon testing; geometry from calibrated CMM measurements of test articles; boundary conditions from ASTM F1717 fixture drawings.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus and yield strength measured from Ti-6Al-4V coupons machined from the same bar stock as test constructs (n=5 coupons per lot). Screw and rod geometry verified by coordinate measuring machine to within 0.02 mm of nominal CAD. ASTM F1717 fixture geometry digitized from manufacturer drawings and confirmed against laboratory fixture photographs. Input uncertainty documented and propagated through UQ campaign."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 constructs tested; samples drawn from production lots; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to nominal geometry within specified tolerances.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories (Lab A: n=6, Lab B: n=5). All constructs drawn from production lots and dimensionally inspected prior to testing. Inter-laboratory variability in stiffness (CV=4.1%) consistent with expected manufacturing and setup variation. Sample size sufficient for statistical comparison at the required credibility level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing performed under at least two independent loading configurations or environmental conditions to bound model applicability; ASTM F1717 protocol followed with documented deviations.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted under a single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration at room temperature only. Required level 3 demands at least two loading configurations; only one was feasible within project scope and timeline. Achieved level 2 reflects full protocol compliance within the single condition but absence of multi-condition coverage. This shortfall is acknowledged as a limitation of the current validation campaign and is flagged in the decision record.",
      "flagged": true
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions) traceable to as-tested experimental conditions; discrepancies quantified and propagated.",
      "rationale": "FEA input parameters set to as-tested values: geometry from CMM of test articles, material properties from lot coupons, boundary conditions from fixture calibration records. Discrepancies between nominal and as-tested geometry quantified (max 0.03 mm); sensitivity to these discrepancies evaluated in UQ campaign and found negligible (<0.5% effect on QoIs). Full traceability matrix provided in supplementary documentation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
