      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval computed for each QoI; acceptance threshold E/uval < 1.96 pre-specified; graphical and tabular comparison provided.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed per ASME V&V 40 Eq. (1) for all three QoIs: stiffness 0.87, yield force 1.31, force at 40 mm 1.58. All below the pre-specified threshold of 1.96. Validation uncertainty uval incorporates experimental measurement uncertainty, numerical solution error, and input parameter uncertainty. Results presented in tabular and graphical form with 95% confidence intervals."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements; linkage documented.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield force are established surrogates for clinical performance in ASTM F1717 regulatory submissions. Force at 40 mm displacement provides a post-yield ductility measure relevant to fatigue and overload scenarios. QoI-to-clinical-endpoint linkage documented via FDA guidance on spinal implant bench testing. All three QoIs are required outputs in the device submission dossier."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments match COU geometry, loading mode, and material system; any gaps between validation and COU conditions documented and bounded.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments performed on the identical non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw geometry under the identical ASTM F1717 compression-bending protocol as the COU. Material system (Ti-6Al-4V), loading mode (static compression-bending), and fixation configuration (bilateral construct, UHMWPE blocks) are fully consistent with the COU. The sole gap — single test condition — is documented under the Test conditions factor and accepted given the Medium assurance level and supporting UQ evidence."
